---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Commercial Door Services Miami, FL | 24/7 Repair & Install"
  description="Commercial door installation, repair, and 24/7 emergency service in Miami, FL. Hurricane-impact, automatic, fire-rated, and high-security storefront doors for Brickell, Wynwood, Coral Gables, Doral, Aventura & beyond. Call (954) 727-5435."
  keywords="commercial door services Miami, commercial door repair Miami FL, commercial door installation Miami, hurricane impact doors Miami, storefront door repair Miami, automatic door repair Miami, fire-rated doors Miami, commercial locksmith Miami, 24/7 commercial door Miami, Brickell commercial door, Wynwood commercial door, Coral Gables commercial door, Doral commercial door, Aventura commercial door, Miami Beach commercial door"
>
  <section class="relative bg-primary text-white py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-cover bg-center opacity-20" style="background-image: url('/images/services/hero.webp')" role="img" aria-label="Commercial door services in Miami Florida"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/95 to-primary/70"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-white">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">›</span> <span class="text-white">Miami, FL</span>
        </nav>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-wide mb-4">Commercial Door Services in Miami, FL</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 mb-8">Hurricane-impact storefront, automatic, fire-rated, and high-security door installation, repair, and maintenance for businesses across Brickell, Wynwood, Coral Gables, Doral, Aventura, Miami Beach, and the rest of South Florida. 24/7 emergency response.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="tel:9547275435" class="bg-white text-primary font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors text-center">(954) 727-5435</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-white hover:text-primary transition-colors text-center">FREE ESTIMATE</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4">Commercial Door Specialists for South Florida</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Miami is one of the most demanding commercial door environments in the country. Salt-laden ocean air corrodes ferrous hardware in months, not years. Hurricane season demands Miami-Dade NOA-approved impact assemblies. Year-round humidity warps wood, blooms aluminum finishes, and seizes hydraulic closers. Add 24/7 hospitality traffic in Brickell, South Beach, and Mid-Beach hotels — and a non-commercial-grade door fails fast.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Our Miami crews specialize in commercial-grade <a href="/service/commercial-door-installation" class="text-accent hover:underline">door installation</a>, emergency <a href="/service/commercial-door-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">door repair</a>, and preventive maintenance built for South Florida's hospitality, retail, marine, healthcare, and logistics sectors. We work with hollow metal, aluminum storefronts, automatic sliders and swingers, fire-rated assemblies, hurricane-impact doors, rolling steel service doors, and high-security entries — for retailers along Lincoln Road, Aventura Mall, Bal Harbour Shops, and the Design District; restaurants in Wynwood, Coconut Grove, and Coral Gables; medical offices around Jackson Memorial and Baptist Health; warehouses in Doral, Hialeah, and the airport-area logistics corridor; and office tenants throughout Brickell, Downtown, and the Miami River district.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">When a panic device fails on a Saturday night in South Beach, when a tropical system shreds an aluminum storefront in Edgewater, or when a high-cycle automatic sliding door at Aventura Mall dies during peak traffic — we respond. 24/7. Locally dispatched. Stocked for the most common commercial hardware brands the day we arrive.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="/images/services/hero.webp" alt="Commercial door installation and repair team serving Miami, Florida" class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Commercial Door Services We Provide in Miami</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">From a stuck back-of-house service door at a Wynwood gallery to a full hurricane-impact storefront retrofit on Collins Avenue, we handle the full lifecycle of commercial entry hardware.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { name: "Commercial Door Installation", href: "/service/commercial-door-installation", desc: "New construction and replacement: hollow metal, aluminum storefront, automatic, hurricane-impact, and fire-rated assemblies — Miami-Dade NOA-approved where required." },
          { name: "Commercial Door Repair", href: "/service/commercial-door-repair", desc: "Sagging doors, broken closers, corroded frames, storm-damaged panels, failed weatherstrip — fixed fast." },
          { name: "Commercial Door Lock Services", href: "/service/commercial-door-lock-services", desc: "Mortise locks, exit devices, electric strikes, master key systems, access control integration — corrosion-resistant for coastal exposure." },
          { name: "Lock Repair", href: "/service/lock-repair", desc: "Sticking cylinders, broken keys, jammed panic bars — rapid response for Miami businesses." },
          { name: "Hinge Repair & Replacement", href: "/service/hinge-repair-replacement", desc: "Continuous hinges, ball-bearing butts, pivot sets — stainless options for salt air, reset for proper alignment and load." },
          { name: "Roller Replacement & Frame Repair", href: "/service/roller-replacement-and-frame-repair", desc: "Sliding-door rollers, tracks, and corroded or bent frames straightened or replaced." },
        ].map((s) => (
          <a href={s.href} class="group block bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 border border-gray-border/30 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-2">{s.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">{s.desc}</p>
            <p class="text-accent text-sm font-heading tracking-wide">Learn More →</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Industries We Serve in Miami</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Different businesses, different door problems. Here is how we tailor commercial door services to Miami's largest commercial sectors.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Hospitality & Hotels</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Hotels along Collins Avenue, Ocean Drive, in Mid-Beach, North Beach, Brickell, and along the Miami River take 24/7 traffic plus salt-air corrosion. We service guest entry doors, automatic operators, electronic access systems, and stairwell fire-doors with minimal disruption to operations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Retail & Storefront</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">High-cycle aluminum storefront and automatic sliding doors at Aventura Mall, Bal Harbour Shops, Dadeland Mall, Dolphin Mall, Brickell City Centre, the Design District, Bayside Marketplace, and Lincoln Road need heavy-duty closers, replaced bottom rails, and hurricane-impact glazing — usually without closing the shop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Restaurants & Bars</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Restaurants in Wynwood, Little Havana, Coconut Grove, Coral Gables (Miracle Mile), and South Beach need code-compliant exit devices, reliable back-of-house service doors, and walk-in cooler hardware that survives Miami humidity and constant temperature swings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Medical & Healthcare</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Medical offices around Jackson Memorial, the University of Miami Health System, Baptist Health South Florida, Mount Sinai, and Mercy Hospital require ADA-compliant automatic operators, hands-free actuation, and fire-rated stairwell assemblies. We handle annual fire-door inspections and hardware retrofits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Warehouse, Logistics & Marine</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Distribution centers in Doral, Hialeah, near Miami International Airport (MIA), and PortMiami rely on rolling steel service doors, hurricane-rated hollow metal entries, and dock-area pedestrian doors. We rebuild fork-truck-hit jambs and replace storm-damaged frames — corrosion-resistant where exposure is high.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Office Towers & Mixed-Use</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Class-A office tenants in Brickell, Downtown Miami, the Miami Worldcenter area, and emerging mixed-use developments in Edgewater and Wynwood need reliable revolving doors, stairwell fire-doors, tenant-suite cylinders, and master key system management.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Miami Neighborhoods & Service Areas We Cover</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Local crews dispatched across Miami-Dade. If you are inside the I-95 / Palmetto / Dolphin Expressway / Turnpike envelope, we are likely already on a job near you today.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
        {[
          "Brickell","Downtown Miami","Miami Worldcenter","Edgewater","Wynwood","Design District","Midtown","Little Havana","Little Haiti","Allapattah","Overtown","Liberty City","Coconut Grove","Coral Gables","Miracle Mile","Doral","Hialeah","Hialeah Gardens","Aventura","North Miami","North Miami Beach","Sunny Isles","Bal Harbour","Surfside","Miami Beach","South Beach","Mid-Beach","North Beach","Key Biscayne","Pinecrest","Kendall","South Miami","Cutler Bay","Homestead","Westchester","Miami Springs","Miami Lakes","MIA Airport Corridor"
        ].map((area) => (
          <span class="bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border border-gray-border/40 text-center">{area}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-sm">Anchored by landmarks like Bayside Marketplace, Bayfront Park, the Pérez Art Museum Miami, the Adrienne Arsht Center, the Kaseya Center, Hard Rock Stadium, Vizcaya Museum and Gardens, the Wynwood Walls, Lincoln Road, Ocean Drive, Aventura Mall, Bal Harbour Shops, Dolphin Mall, Dadeland Mall, Miami International Airport (MIA), and PortMiami — plus surrounding suburbs along I-95, US-1, the Palmetto Expressway, the Dolphin Expressway, Biscayne Boulevard, and Collins Avenue.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-10">Why Miami Businesses Choose Us</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Local, Not a Call Center</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Technicians who know Brickell traffic and the I-95 / Dolphin merge, and route around them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Hurricane-Ready Specs</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Miami-Dade NOA-approved impact assemblies, stainless hardware, marine-grade finishes for salt air.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Code-Aware</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Florida Building Code, Miami-Dade HVHZ, IBC, NFPA 80, and ADA compliance baked into every install.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Real 24/7 Emergency</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">A Saturday night break-in in South Beach gets a tech on-site, not a Monday voicemail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-10">Miami Commercial Door FAQs</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          { q: "Do you offer 24/7 emergency commercial door service in Miami?", a: "Yes. We dispatch emergency commercial door technicians across Miami-Dade 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, including weekends and holidays. Whether your storefront on Collins Avenue was hit overnight, a panic device failed at a Wynwood restaurant, or a sliding door froze open at an Aventura medical office, we respond fast and secure the opening before we leave." },
          { q: "Which Miami neighborhoods do you serve?", a: "We serve all of Miami-Dade — including Brickell, Downtown Miami, Wynwood, the Design District, Edgewater, Coral Gables, Coconut Grove, Doral, Hialeah, Aventura, Sunny Isles, Bal Harbour, Surfside, Miami Beach (South, Mid, and North), Key Biscayne, Pinecrest, Kendall, South Miami, the MIA airport corridor, and points along I-95, US-1, the Palmetto, and the Dolphin Expressway." } ,
          { q: "Do you install Miami-Dade NOA-approved hurricane-impact commercial doors?", a: "Yes. We install Miami-Dade County NOA (Notice of Acceptance) approved hurricane-impact storefront systems, wind-rated hollow metal frames, and laminated glazing assemblies designed for the High-Velocity Hurricane Zone (HVHZ). This is required code in Miami-Dade and a smart upgrade everywhere else in South Florida." },
          { q: "How does Miami salt air affect commercial doors?", a: "Severely. Salt-laden coastal air corrodes ferrous hardware — closers, hinges, lock cylinders, and threshold plates — in months rather than years if the wrong materials are specified. We default to stainless steel and aluminum components on coastal exposures, use marine-grade finishes, and apply protective coatings on door frames where appropriate." },
          { q: "Are your installations Florida Building Code, HVHZ, and ADA compliant?", a: "Yes. Every install is performed to current Florida Building Code, Miami-Dade HVHZ requirements, the International Building Code, NFPA 80 for fire-rated assemblies, and ADA accessibility requirements — including operator force, opening speed, threshold height, and clear-opening width." },
          { q: "Do you handle annual fire-door inspections?", a: "Yes. NFPA 80 requires annual inspection and documentation of all fire-rated door assemblies. We perform the inspection, generate compliance documentation, and complete corrective repairs in a single visit when possible — common for Miami-Dade County Public Schools, hotels, healthcare buildings, and multi-tenant office towers." },
          { q: "What commercial door brands do you service in Miami?", a: "We service all major commercial brands including LCN, Norton, Sargent, Von Duprin, Yale, Schlage, Best, Corbin Russwin, Stanley, Besam/Assa Abloy automatic operators, Horton, Record, and rolling steel from Cornell, Cookson, and Wayne Dalton." }
        ].map((faq) => (
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-border/30">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-heading text-lg tracking-wide text-primary">
              {faq.q}
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-primary text-white text-center">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl tracking-wide mb-4">24/7 Emergency Commercial Door Services in Miami</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">From a busted entry on Lincoln Road to a failed automatic operator at a Brickell tower lobby — call now and a Miami-based technician will be rolling within minutes.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="tel:9547275435" class="bg-accent text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors">Call Now (954) 727-5435</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-white hover:text-primary transition-colors">FREE ESTIMATE</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

